---
import ToolLayout from '../../../Layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import RpeCalculatorContent from '../../../components/content/RpeCalculatorContent.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="RPE Calculator | Weight from RPE, Estimate 1RM & RPE Chart"
  description="Free RPE calculator for strength training. Calculate training weight from RPE, estimate your 1RM, and reference the full RPE-by-reps percentage chart. Mobile-friendly."
  canonicalUrl="https://calcluster.com/tools/rpe-calculator/"
  relatedTools={[
    { name: 'Scale Calculator', link: '/tools/scale-calculator/' },
    { name: 'Right Triangle Calculator', link: '/tools/right-triangle/' },
    { name: 'Ph Calculator', link: '/tools/ph-calculator/' },
  ]}
>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is an RPE calculator used for?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "An RPE calculator converts perceived effort into actual training loads — or works in reverse to estimate a 1RM from a recent set. For someone following effort-based programming, it answers \"what do I actually load?\" For someone without a current tested max, it produces a working estimate without requiring an all-out attempt. Both uses make it a practical daily tool rather than just a static reference."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does RPE 8 mean in the gym?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "RPE 8 means the set was hard, but two more reps were clearly available before failure. It's the most commonly programmed training intensity because it's demanding enough to drive real adaptation while leaving enough reserve to recover well and maintain quality across a full week of training."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between RPE and RIR?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "They're two ways of describing the same thing. RIR, or Reps in Reserve, counts how many reps are left before failure. RPE counts how hard the set felt on a 1–10 scale. The relationship is direct: RPE = 10 − RIR. Two reps left means RIR 2, which equals RPE 8. Some people find RIR more intuitive to judge during a set; RPE shows up more often in written programs. Both systems point to the same underlying effort level."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does e1RM mean?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "e1RM stands for estimated one-rep maximum — a theoretical max calculated from a submaximal set rather than an actual all-out attempt. Lifting 80 kg for 5 reps at RPE 8 produces an e1RM of roughly 98.6 kg using the Tuchscherer table. The calculator uses that figure as the anchor for all subsequent weight recommendations. e1RM and true 1RM aren't always identical, but for day-to-day programming they're close enough — and far safer to obtain regularly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is RPE training better than percentage-based training?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Neither one wins cleanly — they solve different problems. Percentage-based training is simpler and works great when a lifter's strength is relatively predictable. RPE handles the reality that performance varies day to day due to sleep, stress, and accumulated fatigue, which percentages can't account for without constant 1RM retesting. Most well-designed intermediate and advanced programs use both together: percentages to establish the general loading framework, RPE to make it practical on any given training day."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What RPE is best for muscle growth?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Research consistently points to proximity to failure as a key driver of hypertrophy. For most people, the effective range for muscle-building sets lands between RPE 7 and 9, meaning 1–3 reps in reserve. Below RPE 7, sets are generally too far from failure to deliver a meaningful growth stimulus — especially for smaller muscle groups. Grinding out every set to absolute failure (RPE 10) works against the goal too, because the recovery cost outpaces the benefit pretty quickly when done repeatedly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How accurate is this RPE calculator?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For experienced lifters rating effort honestly on shorter sets — particularly 1 to 5 reps — the e1RM estimate tends to land within roughly 5% of a real tested maximum. That's accurate enough to be genuinely useful for programming. Accuracy drops off for higher-rep sets, because perceived exertion tends to plateau before the muscles actually do. The more consistently someone applies the scale across time, the more useful and precise the outputs become."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Who developed the RPE system used in strength training?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The weightlifting-specific 1–10 RPE scale was developed by powerlifting coach Mike Tuchscherer through Reactive Training Systems (RTS) in the early 2000s. The percentage table it generates was later validated scientifically through research by Dr. Eric Helms and Dr. Mike Zourdos, published in the Strength and Conditioning Journal in 2016 — the Helms et al. (2016) paper remains the primary academic reference for RIR-based RPE in resistance training. That research helped bring RPE into mainstream evidence-based programming well beyond the powerlifting community."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does this RPE calculator work for running or cardio?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No — and knowing why helps avoid confusion. The strength training RPE scale is based on reps in reserve and runs from 1 to 10. The Borg scale used in endurance sports runs from 6 to 20 and correlates with heart rate rather than reps. For running, a rough shortcut is to multiply the Borg rating by 10 to estimate heart rate (Borg 14 ≈ 140 bpm). This calculator is built specifically around resistance training and produces reliable results for barbell and strength movements only."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can this tool be used for both bench press and squat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — the calculator doesn't care which exercise is being trained. The math applies to any barbell or strength movement. The one thing worth keeping in mind is that RPE calibration often differs between lifts. A lifter who's been squatting for five years usually reads squat RPE very accurately, while the same person might be less precise on the deadlift if it's a newer movement for them. Tracking RPE per lift, rather than applying a single blanket rating, is what makes the data most useful over time."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the RPE percentage chart and where does it come from?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The RPE percentage chart maps every combination of rep count (1–12) and RPE (6–10 in 0.5 steps) to a corresponding percentage of a lifter's 1RM. The values come from the Reactive Training Systems methodology developed by Mike Tuchscherer. For example, 5 reps at RPE 8 corresponds to 81.1% of 1RM; 3 reps at RPE 9 equals 89.2%. The RPE Chart tab in the calculator above displays the complete table in both list and grid format."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">RPE Calculator — Weight from RPE & 1RM Estimator</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Calculate your working weight based on RPE, estimate your 1RM, or check the RPE chart.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-8 mb-8">
      <!-- LEFT: Calculator Area -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-3">
        
        <!-- Global Unit Toggle -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mb-6" id="unit-toggle">
          <button id="unit-kg-btn" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors">kg</button>
          <button id="unit-lb-btn" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">lb</button>
        </div>

        <!-- Tab Switcher -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-2 mb-6" id="tab-buttons">
          <button data-tab="tab-weight-from-rpe" class="tab-btn w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors">Weight from RPE</button>
          <button data-tab="tab-estimate-1rm" class="tab-btn w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">Estimate 1RM</button>
          <button data-tab="tab-rpe-chart" class="tab-btn w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">RPE Chart</button>
        </div>

        <!-- TAB 1: Weight from RPE -->
        <div id="tab-weight-from-rpe" class="tab-content bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-4 sm:p-6 relative">
          
          <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-5 mb-6">
            <!-- 1RM Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="tm-input" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Your 1RM / Training Max (<span class="unit-label">kg</span>)</label>
              <input type="number" id="tm-input" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 100" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75] transition-all duration-300" />
              <div id="error-tm-1" class="hidden mt-1 text-sm text-red-600"></div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Reps Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="reps-input-1" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Target Reps</label>
              <input type="number" id="reps-input-1" inputmode="decimal" min="1" max="12" step="1" placeholder="e.g. 5" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]" />
              <div id="error-reps-1" class="hidden mt-1 text-sm text-red-600"></div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- RPE Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="rpe-input-1" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Target RPE</label>
              <select id="rpe-input-1" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 bg-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]">
                <option value="10">10</option>
                <option value="9.5">9.5</option>
                <option value="9">9</option>
                <option value="8.5">8.5</option>
                <option value="8" selected>8</option>
                <option value="7.5">7.5</option>
                <option value="7">7</option>
                <option value="6.5">6.5</option>
                <option value="6">6</option>
              </select>
              <div id="warning-rpe-1" class="hidden mt-2 p-3 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 text-amber-700 rounded-lg text-sm"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <button id="calculate-btn-1" class="w-full min-h-[48px] bg-[#1D9E75] hover:bg-[#168561] text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
            Calculate
          </button>

          <!-- Result Card -->
          <div id="result-card-1" class="hidden mt-6 p-6 bg-white border border-[#1D9E75] rounded-xl shadow-sm text-center transition-colors">
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Working Weight</div>
            <div id="result-weight-1" class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 transition-colors">-- <span class="unit-label">kg</span></div>
            <div id="result-percent-1" class="text-slate-600 font-medium">(--% of your 1RM)</div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- TAB 2: Estimate 1RM -->
        <div id="tab-estimate-1rm" class="tab-content hidden bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-4 sm:p-6 relative">
          
          <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 space-y-5 mb-6">
            <!-- Weight Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="weight-input-2" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Weight Lifted (<span class="unit-label">kg</span>)</label>
              <input type="number" id="weight-input-2" inputmode="decimal" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 80" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75] transition-colors duration-300" />
              <div id="error-weight-2" class="hidden mt-1 text-sm text-red-600"></div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Reps Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="reps-input-2" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Reps Performed</label>
              <input type="number" id="reps-input-2" inputmode="decimal" min="1" max="12" step="1" placeholder="e.g. 5" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]" />
              <div id="error-reps-2" class="hidden mt-1 text-sm text-red-600"></div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- RPE Input -->
            <div>
              <label for="rpe-input-2" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">RPE of Set</label>
              <select id="rpe-input-2" class="w-full min-h-[48px] text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 bg-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]">
                <option value="10">10</option>
                <option value="9.5">9.5</option>
                <option value="9">9</option>
                <option value="8.5">8.5</option>
                <option value="8" selected>8</option>
                <option value="7.5">7.5</option>
                <option value="7">7</option>
                <option value="6.5">6.5</option>
                <option value="6">6</option>
              </select>
              <div id="warning-rpe-2" class="hidden mt-2 p-3 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 text-amber-700 rounded-lg text-sm"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <button id="calculate-btn-2" class="w-full min-h-[48px] bg-[#1D9E75] hover:bg-[#168561] text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
            Calculate
          </button>

          <!-- Result Area -->
          <div id="result-area-2" class="hidden mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
            <div id="result-card-2" class="p-6 bg-white border border-[#1D9E75] rounded-xl shadow-sm text-center transition-colors">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Estimated 1RM</div>
              <div id="result-1rm-2" class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2 transition-colors">-- <span class="unit-label">kg</span></div>
              <div id="result-percent-2" class="text-slate-600 font-medium">(based on --% of 1RM at RPE --)</div>
            </div>
            <button id="use-1rm-btn" class="w-full min-h-[48px] border-2 border-[#1D9E75] text-[#1D9E75] hover:bg-[#1D9E75] hover:text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
              Use this 1RM in Weight from RPE &rarr;
            </button>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- TAB 3: RPE Chart -->
        <div id="tab-rpe-chart" class="tab-content hidden bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-xl shadow-sm p-4 sm:p-6 relative">
          
          <!-- View Toggle -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mb-6">
            <button id="chart-view-list" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors">List View</button>
            <button id="chart-view-grid" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">Full Grid</button>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4 sm:p-6 mb-6">
            
            <!-- View 1: List View -->
            <div id="chart-view-list-container">
              <!-- Sub-Mode Toggle -->
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 mb-6">
                <button id="chart-mode-reps" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors">By Reps</button>
                <button id="chart-mode-rpe" class="w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">By RPE</button>
              </div>

              <!-- Mode 1: By Reps -->
              <div id="chart-reps-container">
                <label for="chart-reps-select" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Select Reps</label>
                <select id="chart-reps-select" class="w-full min-h-[48px] mb-4 text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 bg-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]">
                  <!-- Populated by JS (1-12) -->
                </select>
                <div id="chart-reps-list" class="space-y-2 border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                  <!-- Rendered by JS -->
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Mode 2: By RPE -->
              <div id="chart-rpe-container" class="hidden">
                <label for="chart-rpe-select" class="block text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 mb-1">Select RPE</label>
                <select id="chart-rpe-select" class="w-full min-h-[48px] mb-4 text-base border border-slate-300 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-slate-900 bg-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#1D9E75]">
                  <option value="10">10</option>
                  <option value="9.5">9.5</option>
                  <option value="9">9</option>
                  <option value="8.5">8.5</option>
                  <option value="8" selected>8</option>
                  <option value="7.5">7.5</option>
                  <option value="7">7</option>
                  <option value="6.5">6.5</option>
                  <option value="6">6</option>
                </select>
                <div id="chart-rpe-list" class="space-y-2 border-t border-slate-100 pt-4">
                  <!-- Rendered by JS -->
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- View 2: Full Grid -->
            <div id="chart-view-grid-container" class="hidden">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mb-2 block sm:hidden">Scroll &rarr; to see all RPE values</p>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 px-4 sm:mx-0 sm:px-0 pb-2">
                <table class="w-full min-w-[600px] border-collapse bg-white text-sm text-center">
                  <thead class="bg-[#1D9E75]/10 font-semibold text-slate-700">
                    <tr id="chart-grid-header">
                      <!-- Rendered by JS -->
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody id="chart-grid-body">
                    <!-- Rendered by JS -->
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 italic mb-2">Based on the Reactive Training Systems (RTS) RPE chart by Mike Tuchscherer. &mdash; values are estimates; individual results vary.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 italic">&mdash; indicates no published data for this rep/RPE combination.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <!-- end left column -->

      <!-- RIGHT: Ad Sidebar -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 flex justify-center items-start pt-2">
        <div class="w-[300px] h-[250px] bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-slate-400 text-sm">Advertisement</div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- In-content ad -->
    <div class="w-full h-[90px] bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-slate-400 text-sm my-8">Advertisement</div>

    <RpeCalculatorContent />

    <!-- Bottom ad -->
    <div class="w-full h-[90px] bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-slate-400 text-sm my-8">Advertisement</div>

  </div>

  <script>
    (function() {
      // Shared Data across tabs
      // Source: Mike Tuchscherer / Reactive Training Systems RPE chart
      // Values = %1RM for given reps (rows) and RPE (columns)
      // null = no published data for that combination
      const RPE_TABLE = {
        1:  { 10: 100,  9.5: 97.8, 9: 95.5, 8.5: 93.9, 8: 92.2, 7.5: 90.7, 7: 89.2, 6.5: 87.8, 6: 86.3 },
        2:  { 10: 95.5, 9.5: 93.9, 9: 92.2, 8.5: 90.7, 8: 89.2, 7.5: 87.8, 7: 86.3, 6.5: 85.0, 6: 83.7 },
        3:  { 10: 92.2, 9.5: 90.7, 9: 89.2, 8.5: 87.8, 8: 86.3, 7.5: 85.0, 7: 83.7, 6.5: 82.4, 6: 81.1 },
        4:  { 10: 89.2, 9.5: 87.8, 9: 86.3, 8.5: 85.0, 8: 83.7, 7.5: 82.4, 7: 81.1, 6.5: 80.0, 6: 78.9 },
        5:  { 10: 86.3, 9.5: 85.0, 9: 83.7, 8.5: 82.4, 8: 81.1, 7.5: 80.0, 7: 78.9, 6.5: 77.6, 6: 76.2 },
        6:  { 10: 83.7, 9.5: 82.4, 9: 81.1, 8.5: 80.0, 8: 78.9, 7.5: 77.6, 7: 76.2, 6.5: 75.1, 6: 74.0 },
        7:  { 10: 81.1, 9.5: 80.0, 9: 78.9, 8.5: 77.6, 8: 76.2, 7.5: 75.1, 7: 74.0, 6.5: 72.9, 6: 71.7 },
        8:  { 10: 78.9, 9.5: 77.6, 9: 76.2, 8.5: 75.1, 8: 74.0, 7.5: 72.9, 7: 71.7, 6.5: 70.7, 6: 69.4 },
        9:  { 10: 76.2, 9.5: 75.1, 9: 74.0, 8.5: 72.9, 8: 71.7, 7.5: 70.7, 7: 69.4, 6.5: 68.0, 6: 67.4 },
        10: { 10: 74.0, 9.5: 72.9, 9: 71.7, 8.5: 70.7, 8: 69.4, 7.5: 68.0, 7: 67.4, 6.5: 66.0, 6: 65.0 },
        11: { 10: 71.7, 9.5: null, 9: 69.4, 8.5: null, 8: 67.4, 7.5: null, 7: 65.0, 6.5: null, 6: 62.9 },
        12: { 10: 69.4, 9.5: null, 9: 67.4, 8.5: null, 8: 65.0, 7.5: null, 7: 62.9, 6.5: null, 6: 60.8 }
      };
      
      let currentUnit = 'kg';
      const KG_TO_LB = 2.20462;

      function roundWeight(value, unit) {
        const increment = unit === 'kg' ? 2.5 : 5;
        return Math.round(value / increment) * increment;
      }

      // --- Unit Toggle Logic ---
      const unitKgBtn = document.getElementById('unit-kg-btn');
      const unitLbBtn = document.getElementById('unit-lb-btn');
      
      function switchUnit(newUnit) {
        if (newUnit === currentUnit) return;
        const isToLb = newUnit === 'lb';
        currentUnit = newUnit;
        
        if (isToLb) {
          unitLbBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
          unitKgBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        } else {
          unitKgBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
          unitLbBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        }

        // Convert input fields
        if (tmInput.value !== '') {
          const val = parseFloat(tmInput.value);
          tmInput.value = isToLb ? roundWeight(val * KG_TO_LB, 'lb') : roundWeight(val / KG_TO_LB, 'kg');
        }
        if (weightInput2.value !== '') {
          const val = parseFloat(weightInput2.value);
          weightInput2.value = isToLb ? roundWeight(val * KG_TO_LB, 'lb') : roundWeight(val / KG_TO_LB, 'kg');
        }

        // Update DOM labels
        document.querySelectorAll('.unit-label').forEach(el => el.textContent = currentUnit);
        
        // Recalculate results if they are visible, otherwise just reset the empty placeholder labels
        if (!resultCard1.classList.contains('hidden')) {
          calculateTab1();
        } else {
          resultWeight1.innerHTML = `-- <span class="unit-label">${currentUnit}</span>`;
        }
        
        if (!resultArea2.classList.contains('hidden')) {
          calculateTab2();
        } else {
          result1rm2.innerHTML = `-- <span class="unit-label">${currentUnit}</span>`;
        }
      }

      unitKgBtn.addEventListener('click', () => switchUnit('kg'));
      unitLbBtn.addEventListener('click', () => switchUnit('lb'));

      // --- Tab Switching Logic ---
      const tabBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn');
      const tabContents = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
      
      tabBtns.forEach(btn => {
        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const target = btn.getAttribute('data-tab');
          
          tabBtns.forEach(b => {
            if (b.getAttribute('data-tab') === target) {
              b.className = 'tab-btn w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
            } else {
              b.className = 'tab-btn w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
            }
          });
          
          tabContents.forEach(c => {
            if (c.id === target) {
              c.classList.remove('hidden');
            } else {
              c.classList.add('hidden');
            }
          });
        });
      });

      // --- Tab 1: Weight from RPE ---
      const tmInput = document.getElementById('tm-input');
      const repsInput = document.getElementById('reps-input-1');
      const rpeInput = document.getElementById('rpe-input-1');
      const calcBtn1 = document.getElementById('calculate-btn-1');
      
      const errorTm1 = document.getElementById('error-tm-1');
      const errorReps1 = document.getElementById('error-reps-1');
      const warningRpe1 = document.getElementById('warning-rpe-1');
      
      const resultCard1 = document.getElementById('result-card-1');
      const resultWeight1 = document.getElementById('result-weight-1');
      const resultPercent1 = document.getElementById('result-percent-1');

      function validateTab1(showErrors = false) {
        let isValid = true;
        
        errorTm1.classList.add('hidden');
        errorReps1.classList.add('hidden');
        warningRpe1.classList.add('hidden');
        
        const tm = parseFloat(tmInput.value);
        if (isNaN(tm) || tm <= 0) {
          if (showErrors || tmInput.value !== '') {
            errorTm1.textContent = 'Please enter a valid 1RM > 0.';
            errorTm1.classList.remove('hidden');
          }
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const reps = parseInt(repsInput.value, 10);
        if (isNaN(reps) || reps < 1 || reps > 12) {
          if (showErrors || repsInput.value !== '') {
            errorReps1.textContent = 'Reps must be between 1 and 12.';
            errorReps1.classList.remove('hidden');
          }
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const rpe = parseFloat(rpeInput.value);
        if ((reps === 11 || reps === 12) && !Number.isInteger(rpe)) {
          warningRpe1.textContent = "Half-RPE values aren't available for 11-12 reps — please choose a whole-number RPE.";
          warningRpe1.classList.remove('hidden');
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const disableCalc = (reps === 11 || reps === 12) && !Number.isInteger(rpe);
        calcBtn1.disabled = disableCalc;
        calcBtn1.classList.toggle('opacity-50', disableCalc);
        calcBtn1.classList.toggle('cursor-not-allowed', disableCalc);
        
        return isValid;
      }

      function calculateTab1() {
        if (!validateTab1(true)) return;
        
        const tm = parseFloat(tmInput.value);
        const reps = parseInt(repsInput.value, 10);
        const rpe = parseFloat(rpeInput.value);
        
        const percent = RPE_TABLE[reps][rpe];
        
        if (percent === null || percent === undefined) {
          warningRpe1.textContent = "No data available for this combination.";
          warningRpe1.classList.remove('hidden');
          return;
        }
        
        const rawWeight = (tm * percent) / 100;
        const roundedWeight = roundWeight(rawWeight, currentUnit);
        
        resultWeight1.innerHTML = `${roundedWeight} <span class="unit-label">${currentUnit}</span>`;
        resultPercent1.textContent = `(${percent}% of your 1RM)`;
        resultCard1.classList.remove('hidden');
        
        if (window.innerWidth < 640) {
           resultCard1.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
        }
      }

      [tmInput, repsInput, rpeInput].forEach(el => {
        el.addEventListener('input', () => validateTab1(false));
        el.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
          if (e.key === 'Enter') calculateTab1();
        });
      });

      calcBtn1.addEventListener('click', calculateTab1);

      // --- Tab 2: Estimate 1RM ---
      const weightInput2 = document.getElementById('weight-input-2');
      const repsInput2 = document.getElementById('reps-input-2');
      const rpeInput2 = document.getElementById('rpe-input-2');
      const calcBtn2 = document.getElementById('calculate-btn-2');
      
      const errorWeight2 = document.getElementById('error-weight-2');
      const errorReps2 = document.getElementById('error-reps-2');
      const warningRpe2 = document.getElementById('warning-rpe-2');
      
      const resultArea2 = document.getElementById('result-area-2');
      const result1rm2 = document.getElementById('result-1rm-2');
      const resultPercent2 = document.getElementById('result-percent-2');
      const use1rmBtn = document.getElementById('use-1rm-btn');
      
      let lastCalculated1RM = 0;

      function validateTab2(showErrors = false) {
        let isValid = true;
        
        errorWeight2.classList.add('hidden');
        errorReps2.classList.add('hidden');
        warningRpe2.classList.add('hidden');
        
        const weight = parseFloat(weightInput2.value);
        if (isNaN(weight) || weight <= 0) {
          if (showErrors || weightInput2.value !== '') {
            errorWeight2.textContent = 'Please enter a valid weight > 0.';
            errorWeight2.classList.remove('hidden');
          }
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const reps = parseInt(repsInput2.value, 10);
        if (isNaN(reps) || reps < 1 || reps > 12) {
          if (showErrors || repsInput2.value !== '') {
            errorReps2.textContent = 'Reps must be between 1 and 12.';
            errorReps2.classList.remove('hidden');
          }
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const rpe = parseFloat(rpeInput2.value);
        if ((reps === 11 || reps === 12) && !Number.isInteger(rpe)) {
          warningRpe2.textContent = "Half-RPE values aren't available for 11-12 reps — please choose a whole-number RPE.";
          warningRpe2.classList.remove('hidden');
          isValid = false;
        }
        
        const disableCalc = (reps === 11 || reps === 12) && !Number.isInteger(rpe);
        calcBtn2.disabled = disableCalc;
        calcBtn2.classList.toggle('opacity-50', disableCalc);
        calcBtn2.classList.toggle('cursor-not-allowed', disableCalc);
        
        return isValid;
      }

      function calculateTab2() {
        if (!validateTab2(true)) return;
        
        const weight = parseFloat(weightInput2.value);
        const reps = parseInt(repsInput2.value, 10);
        const rpe = parseFloat(rpeInput2.value);
        
        const percent = RPE_TABLE[reps][rpe];
        
        if (percent === null || percent === undefined) {
          warningRpe2.textContent = "No data available for this combination.";
          warningRpe2.classList.remove('hidden');
          return;
        }
        
        const estimated1RM = weight / (percent / 100);
        const roundedResult = roundWeight(estimated1RM, currentUnit);
        lastCalculated1RM = roundedResult;
        
        result1rm2.innerHTML = `${roundedResult} <span class="unit-label">${currentUnit}</span>`;
        resultPercent2.textContent = `(based on ${percent}% of 1RM at RPE ${rpe})`;
        resultArea2.classList.remove('hidden');
        
        if (window.innerWidth < 640) {
           resultArea2.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
        }
      }

      [weightInput2, repsInput2, rpeInput2].forEach(el => {
        el.addEventListener('input', () => validateTab2(false));
        el.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
          if (e.key === 'Enter') calculateTab2();
        });
      });

      calcBtn2.addEventListener('click', calculateTab2);

      // Cross-tab handoff logic
      use1rmBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        // Switch to Tab 1
        const tab1Btn = document.querySelector('.tab-btn[data-tab="tab-weight-from-rpe"]');
        if (tab1Btn) tab1Btn.click();
        
        // Populate 1RM in Tab 1
        tmInput.value = lastCalculated1RM;
        validateTab1(false);
        
        // Briefly highlight the populated input
        tmInput.classList.add('ring-2', 'ring-[#1D9E75]', 'bg-[#1D9E75]/10');
        setTimeout(() => {
          tmInput.classList.remove('ring-2', 'ring-[#1D9E75]', 'bg-[#1D9E75]/10');
        }, 1200);
        
        // Scroll up to the input if on mobile
        if (window.innerWidth < 640) {
           tmInput.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
        }
      });

      // --- Tab 3: RPE Chart ---
      const chartViewListBtn = document.getElementById('chart-view-list');
      const chartViewGridBtn = document.getElementById('chart-view-grid');
      const chartViewListContainer = document.getElementById('chart-view-list-container');
      const chartViewGridContainer = document.getElementById('chart-view-grid-container');

      const chartModeReps = document.getElementById('chart-mode-reps');
      const chartModeRpe = document.getElementById('chart-mode-rpe');
      const chartRepsContainer = document.getElementById('chart-reps-container');
      const chartRpeContainer = document.getElementById('chart-rpe-container');
      const chartRepsSelect = document.getElementById('chart-reps-select');
      const chartRpeSelect = document.getElementById('chart-rpe-select');
      const chartRepsList = document.getElementById('chart-reps-list');
      const chartRpeList = document.getElementById('chart-rpe-list');
      
      let currentChartMode = 'reps';

      function renderRepsList() {
        const reps = parseInt(chartRepsSelect.value, 10);
        const data = RPE_TABLE[reps];
        chartRepsList.innerHTML = '';
        const rpeValues = [10, 9.5, 9, 8.5, 8, 7.5, 7, 6.5, 6];
        
        rpeValues.forEach(rpe => {
          const pct = data[rpe];
          const pctText = pct !== null ? `${pct}%` : '&mdash;';
          chartRepsList.innerHTML += `
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-3 text-slate-700">
              <span class="font-medium text-slate-900">RPE ${rpe}</span>
              <span class="font-semibold ${pct !== null ? 'text-[#1D9E75]' : 'text-slate-400'}">${pctText}</span>
            </div>
          `;
        });
      }

      function renderRpeList() {
        const rpe = parseFloat(chartRpeSelect.value);
        chartRpeList.innerHTML = '';
        
        for (let reps = 1; reps <= 12; reps++) {
          const pct = RPE_TABLE[reps][rpe];
          const pctText = pct !== null ? `${pct}%` : '&mdash;';
          const repLabel = reps === 1 ? '1 rep' : `${reps} reps`;
          chartRpeList.innerHTML += `
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center bg-slate-50 rounded-lg p-3 text-slate-700">
              <span class="font-medium text-slate-900">${repLabel}</span>
              <span class="font-semibold ${pct !== null ? 'text-[#1D9E75]' : 'text-slate-400'}">${pctText}</span>
            </div>
          `;
        }
      }

      // View Toggles
      chartViewListBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        chartViewListBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
        chartViewGridBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        chartViewListContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
        chartViewGridContainer.classList.add('hidden');
      });

      chartViewGridBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        chartViewGridBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
        chartViewListBtn.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        chartViewGridContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
        chartViewListContainer.classList.add('hidden');
        renderFullGrid();
      });

      let isGridRendered = false;
      function renderFullGrid() {
        if (isGridRendered) return;
        const header = document.getElementById('chart-grid-header');
        const body = document.getElementById('chart-grid-body');

        const rpes = [10, 9.5, 9, 8.5, 8, 7.5, 7, 6.5, 6];

        let ths = `<th class="sticky left-0 bg-[#e5f5ef] px-3 py-3 border-r border-slate-200 z-20 w-24"></th>`;
        rpes.forEach(r => {
          ths += `<th class="px-3 py-3 whitespace-nowrap">RPE ${r}</th>`;
        });
        header.innerHTML = ths;

        let rows = '';
        for (let reps = 1; reps <= 12; reps++) {
          const isEven = reps % 2 === 0;
          const bgClass = isEven ? 'bg-slate-50' : 'bg-white';
          
          let tr = `<tr class="${bgClass}">`;
          tr += `<th class="sticky left-0 ${bgClass} px-3 py-3 border-r border-slate-200 font-medium text-slate-900 z-10 text-left whitespace-nowrap">${reps} rep${reps > 1 ? 's' : ''}</th>`;

          rpes.forEach(rpe => {
            const val = RPE_TABLE[reps][rpe];
            const text = val !== null ? `${val}%` : '&mdash;';
            const textClass = val !== null ? 'text-slate-700' : 'text-slate-300';
            tr += `<td class="px-3 py-3 ${textClass} border-slate-100 ${rpe !== 6 ? 'border-r' : ''}">${text}</td>`;
          });
          tr += `</tr>`;
          rows += tr;
        }
        body.innerHTML = rows;
        isGridRendered = true;
      }

      chartModeReps.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (currentChartMode === 'reps') return;
        currentChartMode = 'reps';
        chartModeReps.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
        chartModeRpe.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        chartRepsContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
        chartRpeContainer.classList.add('hidden');
      });

      chartModeRpe.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (currentChartMode === 'rpe') return;
        currentChartMode = 'rpe';
        chartModeRpe.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-[#1D9E75] text-white transition-colors';
        chartModeReps.className = 'w-full min-h-[48px] px-2 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg bg-white text-slate-600 border border-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors';
        chartRpeContainer.classList.remove('hidden');
        chartRepsContainer.classList.add('hidden');
        renderRpeList();
      });

      chartRepsSelect.addEventListener('change', renderRepsList);
      chartRpeSelect.addEventListener('change', renderRpeList);
      
      // Populate initial reps options and render
      for(let i = 1; i <= 12; i++) {
        const opt = document.createElement('option');
        opt.value = i;
        opt.textContent = i;
        chartRepsSelect.appendChild(opt);
      }
      renderRepsList();
    })();
  </script>
</ToolLayout>